The Turkish producer of Power Black, a premium energy drink, says it is targeting a significant share of the Nigerian drink market as it steps up efforts to replicate its success in over 35 countries where the product is currently sold. Ares Gida Manufacturing of Turkey said it had partnered with Frisson Nigeria Limited, the sole distributor of the energy drink in Nigeria, to introduce the product into the Nigeria market. A representative of the Ares Gida Manufacturing, Turkey, Mr. Recep Yildiz, was quoted in a statement as saying this during the launch of the product in Lagos. According to him, the product is currently a leading brand in the energy drink market in Spain, Germany, United Arab Emirate, Kuwait, Qatar, Jordan, Chad, Ghana, Ivory Coast and Mali. As such, Yildiz expressed confidence that the brands would soon take a leadership position in the Nigeria market. The Marketing Manager, Frisson Nigeria, Mr. Ojotobor Samuel, who believe the energy drink will offer the consumers the power to achieve their goals with class and finesse, said Nigeria joined other countries in Europe, Asia and other continents where the product had been introduced.